TITLE      Proton capture cross section of 7Be and the flux of
            high energy solar neutrinos
FACILITY   (DYNAM,1USAANL) Argonne National laboratory 4.5 MV
            dynamitron.
SAMPLE     7Be produced via the 7Li(p,n)7Be reaction.
           Final target consisted of 80 mCi of 7Be (0.23 microg)
            and 7 microg of solids
METHOD     Sawtooth-wave voltage applied to two orthogonal sets
            of parallel plates (at incommensurate frequencies)
            prior to beam collimation in order to ensure a stable,
            uniform beam spot.
DETECTOR   (SOLST) Silicon surface-barrier detector with 300 mm2
            active area and 23 microm depletion depth.
MONITOR    (3-LI-7(D,P)3-LI-8,,SIG) 7Be areal density.
           Energy scale of dymanitron determined from
            19F(p,alpha gamma) thick target yields at 224.4,
            340.46, and 872.11 keV resonances.
           7Be areal density measured
            1) relative to yield of 7Li(d,p)8Li reaction at
               0.77-MeV resonance.
            2) using yield of 478-keV gamas in Ge(Li) detector
               whose efficiency found using calibrated gamma
               sources of 54Mn, 133Ba, and 137Cs.
           Solid angle of detector determined by comparing alpha
            particle yield with 7Li(d,p)8Li->8Be*->2alpha in the
            near geometry (2 mm target-collimator distance) to
            that in a far geometry (target-collimator distance
            22.2mm).
DECAY-DATA (5-B-8,0.769SEC)
DECAY-MON  (3-LI-8,0.842SEC)
CORRECTION Total number of 7Be nuclei corrected for decay.
           Data corrected for:
           . background,
           . alphas below cutoff energy of 0.95 MeV,
           . energy loss of beam in target,
ERR-ANALYS (ERR-S) Uncertainty due to counting statistics.
STATUS     No reply from B. Filippone to author proof.
